begin_memory_text: We talked about where I'm from, and at first I tried to explain just the general geography of it in terms of the area of the state, but it didn't really work, so I tried to explain in terms of proximity to well known cities; eventually he just looked at a map.
middle_memory_text: We talked about different stuff about the area I live in mainly, like what it's like to live here, what the weather is like, what there is to do here. He talked about how he doesn't really think of Washington as being rural, things like that. I asked a little bit about where he's from (Pittsburgh) and we talked about Michigan a little bit.
end_memory_text: We talked some more about Washington, Michigan, Pennsylvania, the weather, climates, etc. We talked about pollution and I talked about how the Cuyahoga River caught on fire before, and about how Lake Erie is polluted, and some stuff like that. We also talked about living in cities vs. living out in the country.
rest_of_day_open: I'll need to spend a lot of time stacking the rest of the firewood that's been split so that it doesn't get too wet, and especially so that it doesn't get snowed on; it's supposed to already snow this coming weekend. I hope to get some work done and make some money, and I also want to do some work on learning Python and HTML. Maybe I'll work on some hobbies as well. I'll probably socialize with some friends online and maybe talk to a friend or two on the phone.
critical_positive: I think we got along well and my conversation partner was pleasant, and hopefully I was as well. It was nice that he was interested in things I could say a lot about (where I'm from) and that we both seemed to enjoy talking about that kind of thing, and that we seemed to enjoy talking to each other.
critical_negative: I think maybe I could have asked a little bit more about him and asked him more questions and not talked so much the whole time. To be fair, though, he seemed to be interested in asking me questions and listening about stuff. I don't think there was a lot that didn't work well other than that.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where he lived and the weather there. Also, the mountain range and dryness toward the east. We talked about the area and what it is near.
middle_memory_text: We talked about the rural setting, and how surprising it is to me that Washington state has the rural areas. I told him it seems so foreign. We talked about the Columbia River and fishing. We talked about goeyducks.
end_memory_text: We talked about his proximity to Oregon. Gas and food price differences in each state. Also, hunting, and the fact they have whitetail deer and elk. We talked about farming, different crops they grow there and the high desert in Washington.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will go well. It is the beginning of the week, so I hope to accomplish alot of things. It was a busy day today, so I am hoping to unwind and relax a bit and help the kids out. I am looking forward to doing things with the kids like we did last weekend.
critical_positive: I asked alot of questions due to my interest in the area he is living in. I listened and tried to learn. I would also discuss things in my area and try to keep a dialogue. I asked questions about the cost of living, so these sparked alot of dialogue.
critical_negative: It seemed when I stopped talking he would not have anything to say. It would have been awkward if I did not keep bringing up questions or information about myself. He was friendly and talked well, but did not have many questions. I could have talked more about myself instead of questioning him so much; I was just interested in his environment.
